derivation.yuyuan_name: mid 16th cent.: from medieval Latin coincident- 'coinciding, agreeing', from the verb coincidere (see coincide)

entry.def: Coincident events happen at the same time.

example.ex: Coincident with the talks, the bank was permitted to open a New York branch.
example.tran: 会谈的同时，该银行已获准在纽约开设分行。

entry.def: Coincident opinions, ideas, or policies are the same or are very similar to each other.

example.ex: Their aims are coincident with ours...
example.tran: 他们的目标与我们的一致。

example.ex: Coincident interests with the corporate rich and political directorate are pointed out.
example.tran: 有人指出这合乎的是公司富豪和政治官员的利益。
